      "note_no": "32",
      "note": "Or: \"brings about [the fulfilment of] His command\". This may be an allusion to the Day of Judgment or - more probably - to the inevitable degeneration and decline of communities which place narrow self-interest above ethical values. In particular, this passage rejects the tendency to regard ties of kinship and national affiliation (expressed in the term \"your clan\") as the decisive factors of social behaviour, and postulates ideology (\"God and His Apostle and the struggle in His cause\") as the only valid basis on which a believer's life - individually and socially - should rest."
